Certainly! Here's an example of how you can implement lazy loading to delay the loading of ads using the Intersection Observer API:

```html
<!-- Placeholders for ad containers -->
<div class="ad-container" id="ad-container-1"></div>
<div class="ad-container" id="ad-container-2"></div>

<script>
function loadAds(entry) {
  // Load ad code into the ad container
  const adContainer = entry.target;
  const adCode = `<script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-3497341338386784"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <!-- Solitaire | Square Banner 1 -->
  <ins class="adsbygoogle"
      style="display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px"
      data-ad-client="ca-pub-3497341338386784"
      data-ad-slot="9927467076"></ins>
  <script>
      (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
  </script>`;
  adContainer.innerHTML = adCode;
}

// Create an Intersection Observer instance
const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries, observer) => {
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
      // When the ad container comes into view, load the ad code
      loadAds(entry);
      // Stop observing the ad container
      observer.unobserve(entry.target);
    }
  });
});

// Select the ad containers and start observing them
const adContainers = document.querySelectorAll('.ad-container');
adContainers.forEach(adContainer => {
  observer.observe(adContainer);
});
</script>
```

In this example, we have two ad container divs with the class "ad-container." The Intersection Observer API is used to monitor when these ad containers enter the viewport. Once an ad container comes into view, the `loadAds` function is called, which replaces the placeholder content with the actual ad code.

By using this approach, the ad code will only be loaded and displayed when the ad container is visible to the user, reducing the initial load time of the ads. Additionally, the observer will stop observing the ad container after it has loaded the ad code to optimize performance.

Make sure to replace the ad code in the `loadAds` function with your own ad code obtained from your ad provider, such as Google AdSense.

Note: This example assumes that you have already included the necessary Google AdSense script in the head section of your HTML file.

